The Mediterranean Fever Treatment Market can be segmented based on treatment type, distribution channel, and region. In terms of treatment type, the market offers options such as colchicine, corticosteroids, nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs), and interferon. Colchicine is commonly used in managing and preventing attacks of familial Mediterranean fever (FMF). Corticosteroids and NSAIDs are also utilized to reduce inflammation and pain associated with the condition. Interferon is another treatment option that has shown promise in certain cases. Regarding distribution channels, patients can access Mediterranean fever treatments through hospital pharmacies, retail pharmacies, or online pharmacies. The regional segmentation includes North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, Latin America, and the Middle East & Africa, each offering unique market dynamics and growth opportunities.

